attributes.Long form description: The student starts by disassembling the two joy-con controllers the Nintendo and putting them into the comfort grip, then disassembling the comfort grip and putting them into the joy-con straps, and finally putting the two joy-con controllers into the Nintendo again and then placing the Nintendo and changing the game card and the sd card, and finally, turn on and off the console.

attributes.Transcription: Okay
please change the controllers from the handheld mode to the joycon comfort grip, which is the big controller in front of you.

attributes.Action sentence: The student dettaches the joycon controllers.

attributes.Transcription: So take the red and blue controllers off the Nintendo Switch.
You have to press the button which is on the back.
Let's unlocked it.
And put the red and blue controller into the big controller that you see in front of you.

attributes.Action sentence: The student inserts the joy con controllers into the comfort grip.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Didnt put the controller correctly, with (-) and (+)

attributes.Transcription: You have to match the red and the plus on the plus, and the minus on the minus, so currently they lined up.
Well done.
Now please change the controller from the comfort grip to the individual joy con grips, So the two grips lined up next to you.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the joy-con controller to the individual handheld grip.

attributes.Transcription: Ups.
You put it on the wrong one, maybe try to pull it out again.
And you can attach the plus on the plus and the minus on the minus.
Now you also need to press down the white thing at the bottom of the controller, so that actually locks it.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student understands he needs to pull the joy con strap lock.

attributes.Transcription: Press the button.
Yes.
Perfect.
Now please change the controllers back to the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student inserts the joy con controller into the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: It is not correctly inserted on the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: You need to slide it from the top to the bottom.
Well done.
Now please put out the kickstand of the Nintendo Switch, it is on the back of the nintendo switch and you have to pull it out.

attributes.Action sentence: The student pulls out the kickstand from the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The students could not open the kickstand

attributes.Transcription: You just need to pull it out towards to you.
And put down the Switch in front of you, standing up.
Hold on.
Now please change the game card of the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the game card of the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: The game card is at the top rigth, you just have to open it.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student pulls the game card but he should push it in order to take it out.
The student pushes the game card without enough force.

attributes.Transcription: You need to press down on the game card.
And then you have a game in your back rigth? the new game.
Well done.
Now change the micro sd card on the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the sd card of the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: The micro sd card is behind the kickstand.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student didnÂ´t push strong enough.
The student should not pull the sd card, he should push it.

attributes.Transcription: You should be able to just pull it out.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The sd card should be pushed not pulled out.

attributes.Transcription: Well done.
You can close the kickstand.
Now please turn on the Nintendo Switch.
There's a button on the top left, which you can push.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: Well done.
Now please turn off the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: You need to go to the power options and then turn it off.
Perfect.
You can stop the recording now.
